title: For Sale/Trade:  1918 Lithgow No. I Mk. III Lee Enfield
postcontent:
1918 Lithgow No. I Mk. III Lee Enfield.  Manufactured in Australia's Lithgow factory in 1918, served with the 3rd Division, 2nd Military District (Eastern Command, New South Wales).  Some amazing history behind this rifle.

It's all original (except the sling) and all matching numbers (23400 s/n) Has normal marks of a gun that is 100 years old that has never been refinished.  Metal and bore are solid, no distinctive pitting or rust. The brass stock disk is missing but they can be replaced for about 10 bucks at any large gun show or via ebay.  Would make a great collector's piece or historical shooter.  Shoots very accurately for a 100 year old gun and bolt is buttery smooth.  

Will come with a surplus sling, one magazine (sn matches the gun,) and 65 rounds of ammo.

Asking 500 due to it being unmodified from its original condition.

title: For Sale:  Leman Conversion M1816 Musket
postcontent:
This is a solid example of a M. T. Wickham contract M1816 musket converted to percussion by Leman. This example is full length, and unmodified. The ramrod is unfortunately broken to 33 inches in length, and there is a sliver of wood missing to the side of the tang (a common problem with converted muskets if the lock screws weren't loosened before the barrel was removed). The lock functions very well, and all internal parts have the same mating marks. The cone is in good shape, and air easily passes through the barrel. The cleanout screw is removable. The bore is dark, but would probably clean out better if so desired. No cartouches are present on the stock, but is does not appear to have been sanded. The barrel bands retain much of the original national armoury brown lacquer finish. 

I can arrange for shipping if need be, but will also meet in person if you are in the area.

postcontent:
To replace your exsisting standard fixed front sight on your AR15, M16, M4.

The VST folding front sight and gas block is an all-steel, flip-up design, with spring loaded detents. There is no lock so if the sight gets hit, the sight will fold down rather than damage a locking mechanism. The VST-1 series incorporates a QD sling swivel cup mount while the VST-2 does not.  All models use an AK47/AKM/AK74 front sight post. This allows the user adjust the sight, for elevation, with the use of a simple AK cleaning kit.

Despite the VST's solid construction, it actually weighs less than a standard A2 front sight tower.

The clamping system has been carefully designed to provide an unparalleled hold when installed properly.  During testing, the VST-1 withstood over 100 ft/lbs of rotational torque and is stronger than the barrel’s receiver indexing pin.
CASV: AR-15 HANDGUARD
CASV: AR-15 Handguard
Originally developed for the US Navy E.O.D. (Explosive Ordnance Disposal) Groups, the CASV handguard is a drop-on rail system for any AR-15 platform equipped with an M4 flat top receiver and fixed front sight post.  Used it for a month  pretty brand new, working on new project.
